{
  "stem": "27507.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The children were-- would just go under the wall through a hole in the wall, over the wall and go into the Polish part of Warsaw with some money and buy something, like buy a few pounds of potatoes, or bread or something else and try to smuggle themselves again through the ghetto in different ways.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Sometimes climbing over the wall, sometimes scrambling under the wall if there was a hole.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Sometimes, because there were gates and those gates were-- the gates were-- in the wall, there were places where you-- of passage between the-- between the Polish and-- part and the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And that was called [NON-ENGLISH] because the German word is-- wache is guard.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They were guarded by-- there were-- by German, German gendarmerie, Polish police, which were so-called blue police, the navy blue police because of the uniform they called, and Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And they all were guarding it, and the gate was, from time to time, being opened, and then they would allow whoever was allowed, whether it was a car or a cart or somebody to enter the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And sometimes the gate was opened for a bit longer because something like a lorry would need to come.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then sometimes the children would try to run through to rush the gate, and some of them would be shot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Every time, some of them would be shot.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Some would get caught, and then they would have to empty their clothes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And whatever they had in the way of supply, it would be confiscated, and they would be probably taken to prison or beaten up and so on.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "It was-- and some would get through.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But many more would get over the wall or under the wall.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
